HUMAN Settlements Minister Nomaindia Mfeketo will today hand over title deeds and houses in Delft Precinct 7 at the N2 Gateway Delft Precinct 7 at the N2 Gateway. Mfeketo said the handing over of houses and more than 2000 title deeds in Delft would prioritise, among others, senior citizens, child-headed households and people living with disabilities. She said the title deeds restorationÂ programme was aimed at ensuring complete property ownership by historically disadvantaged people of South Africa. Mfeketo will be accompanied by her deputy, Zou Kota-Fredericks, human settlements MECs from different provinces and executive mayors from metropolitan municipalities. -Afro Reporter